\
K-Nearest Neighbors allows us to predict the discrete value (category) of a new example.\
\
Steps of KNN\
1. Choose number of neighbors K\
2. Find the nearest neighbors K of the new data point, according to Euclidean\
distance\
3. Among the K neighbors, count the number of data points in each category\
4. The category with the most data points represented in this selection is\
the one you assign your new data point to}